page.title: 09LEISURE.Birds.
page.content: BIRDS. Trosley Country Park is 160 acres in size and is a home for many wild birds and animals .Some of the most common birds are magpies,jays,swallows,bluetits, thrushes and sparrows. Our summer visitors are whitethroats,lesser whitethroats,housemarten and swifts. There are three types of woodpecker in the park.They are the green woodpecker,the great spotted woodpecker and the lesser spotted woodpecker.The lesser spotted woodpeckeris not so rare as the other two.Hoopoes do not come from this country but one has been spotted in Trosley.Other rare birds in the park are the firecrest and the tawny owl.
